12
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,920
Do you really know magic?

13
00:02:23,170 --> 00:02:24,329
Of course not.

14
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,780
How did you know about the rain in Yuzhou?

15
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:28,579
This news

16
00:02:28,850 --> 00:02:30,310
was only delivered today.

17
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:32,660
I was just lucky.

18
00:02:33,540 --> 00:02:36,570
I went to buy some vegetables before entering the palace that day.

19
00:02:36,570 --> 00:02:38,140
I happened to meet a vegetable farmer.

20
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:41,000
He told me that there's heavy mist in the mountains.

21
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:42,540
The north wind started up,

22
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:44,540
so the mist would float to Yuzhou.

23
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:46,670
When this kind of weather occurs in the winter,

24
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:48,070
it will definitely rain.

25
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,410
An important figure like you

26
00:02:50,410 --> 00:02:51,760
still cares for the commoners.

27
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:52,520
I admire you.

28
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:54,270
What important figure?

29
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,730
We still need to eat vegetables and porridge.

30
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,880
By the way, Lord Yang,

31
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:00,650
later,

32
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,300
you must do me a favor.

33
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:03,400
What is it?

34
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:10,510
Eunuch Wang.

35
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:13,120
Imperial Preceptor.

36
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,680
What is this place?

37
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:18,840
It's just a wasteland that has been abandoned for 100 years.

38
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,010
Let's go on.

39
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:21,000
Wait.

40
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:23,990
I think this place has great feng shui.

41
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:26,530
It has the potential to be the site of a pagoda.

42
00:03:26,530 --> 00:03:28,390
This place...

43
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,760
It's a place of bad luck in the palace.

44
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:33,100
Imperial Preceptor, are you mistaken?

45
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:33,820
No.

46
00:03:34,579 --> 00:03:37,180
This place is just deserted,

47
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,760
but there are treasures hidden throughout.

48
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:42,420
Well, Imperial Preceptor,

49
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,950
I am speaking the truth.

50
00:03:45,530 --> 00:03:48,540
This was where the late Empress Dowager Kang Xian lived.

51
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,100
